    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with **Jackson Merrill** (72.75) and **Kyle Tucker** (72.04) anchoring our production as the clear elite starts. **Jackson Merrill** is a priority play against Burke; not only is he hitting in the premium #3 spot, but the combination of a favorable platoon advantage and an opposing starter with a slow delivery provides an optimal runway for his high-end stolen base potential. Similarly, **Kyle Tucker** benefits from a high-efficiency matchup against McGreevy, where his elevated base projection is further bolstered by a strong park factor and a favorable order placement. **Drake Baldwin** rounds out our top-tier tier with a 67.34 rating; despite a neutral platoon, his spot at #2 and favorable park context make him a high-floor asset for today\u2019s rotations.\n\nOur most difficult roster decision came down to **Coby Mayo**, who finished with a 52.17 score\u2014only a narrow margin behind **Josh Lowe** (49.34) and **Marcell Ozuna** (56.26). Ultimately, the optimizer favored the specific platoon dynamics of **Josh Lowe** and the raw projection of **Marcell Ozuna** against Lowder, despite **Coby Mayo** providing a slight theoretical boost via the slow delivery of Weathers. Elsewhere, we remain cautious regarding **Gunnar Henderson** (55.17); while his speed remains a critical weapon, the significant platoon penalty against the southpaw Weathers suppresses his overall efficiency score, necessitating a move out of the high-output tier.\n\nRisks for today are largely centered around our exposure to left-handed pitching. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (58.22) faces a tough test in Prielipp, where his raw power is slightly dampened by the pitcher\u2019s skill, and **Nasim Nunez** (47.54) continues to struggle for efficiency while batting in the #8 hole against Harrison. While **Josh Lowe** has a strong platoon edge, the 2.95 xERA of McLean stands as the most daunting individual matchup for any of our starters. We are prioritizing speed and high-order placement to navigate these hurdles, keeping our bench options like **Miguel Vargas** and **Brady House** ready should any last-minute lineup adjustments shift the platoon advantage in our favor.",
